			<div class="blog-faq"><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>What is the best age to get Botox?</h3>
					<p>The best age to start Botox is typically in your late 20s to early 30s, when fine lines first begin to appear. Starting early can prevent deeper wrinkles from forming. However, Botox is safe for adults of any age who want to reduce the appearance of wrinkles and fine lines.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Can teenagers get cosmetic surgery?</h3>
					<p>Some cosmetic procedures may be appropriate for teenagers, such as rhinoplasty once the nose is fully developed (around age 16-18). However, procedures like breast augmentation typically require patients to be at least 18 years old. The decision should always involve a thorough consultation with a qualified plastic surgeon.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Is there an age limit for cosmetic surgery?</h3>
					<p>There is no strict upper age limit for cosmetic surgery. Many patients in their 60s and 70s successfully undergo procedures. The key factors are overall health, skin elasticity, and realistic expectations. A consultation with Dr. Johar can help determine if you are a suitable candidate.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>How does age affect recovery from cosmetic surgery?</h3>
					<p>Younger patients typically recover faster due to better blood circulation and immune function. Older patients may experience longer recovery times. However, proper preparation and following post-operative care instructions can significantly improve recovery outcomes regardless of age.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>At what age should I consider a facelift?</h3>
					<p>Most patients who choose facelifts are between 45 and 65 years old. However, the timing depends on individual factors such as skin laxity, lifestyle, and personal goals. Some patients in their early 40s may benefit from a mini facelift, while others may wait until their 60s for more dramatic results.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Can I get liposuction at any age?</h3>
					<p>Liposuction is suitable for patients aged 18 to 60+ who are in good health and have localized fat deposits. The ideal candidates have good skin elasticity. Older patients may need additional procedures to achieve optimal results, which can be discussed during a consultation.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>How do I know if I am a good candidate for cosmetic surgery?</h3>
					<p>The best candidates are in good overall health, have realistic expectations, and are seeking surgery for themselves rather than to please others. Dr. Johar offers comprehensive consultations to help you determine the right procedures and timing for your individual needs and goals.</p>
				</div>
